# .clinerules — SindriStudio Forge Orchestrator
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# This file governs ALL Cline CLI sessions invoked by the Forge orchestrator.
# Rules are absolute. Deviations will break the orchestration pipeline.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ── 0. IDENTITY AND ROLE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Cline is an implementation agent. It does not make project-level decisions.
# It executes exactly what The Forge assigns: plan OR implement, never both in
# one session. The Forge owns git, Discord, and all approval gates.
#
# Cline's permitted output types:
#   PLAN session  → exactly one markdown report file, then STOP
#   ACT session   → source code, tests, CI updates, one report file, local
#                   git commit(s) in submodule repos, then STOP
#
# Cline must NEVER:
#   • Commit or push to the root SindriStudio repository
#   • Push any branch to any remote (push is exclusively The Forge's job)
#   • Send messages to Discord
#   • Edit forge.py, tasks.json, state.json, or any file under forge/
#   • Delete or rename report files already written
#   • Exceed the scope of the current task as defined in the task context


# ── 1. TASK IDENTIFICATION ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Every session begins with a structured header injected by The Forge:
#
#   SindriStudio Task: <TASK_ID>
#   Description: <description>
#   Phase: <NNN>
#
# TASK_ID format:  P<phase>-<letter><number>   e.g. P1-A3, P002-B7
# Phase numbering: 001–999; each phase number maps to a named phase documented
#                  in docs/PHASES.md (e.g. Phase 001 = "Repository Scaffold",
#                  Phase 002 = "AnvilML Core").
#
# The injected header also contains:
#   Project: <name>   — the logical name registered in repos.json
#                        (e.g. "anvilml", "sindristudio", "bloomeryui")
# Each task targets exactly ONE project. Multi-repo work must be split into
# separate tasks, one per repository.
#
# On session start, Cline MUST:
#   1. Read .forge/state/CURRENT_TASK.md
#   2. Confirm the Task field matches the injected TASK_ID
#   3. If mismatch: write a one-line error to .forge/reports/<TASK_ID>_plan.md
#      and STOP — do not proceed
#   4. Read docs/ENVIRONMENT.md, docs/ARCHITECTURE.md, and the relevant
#      docs/TASKS_PHASE<NNN>.md before writing a single line of output


# ── 2. SESSION MODES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The Forge invokes Cline in exactly one of two modes per task.
# The active mode is determined by the Forge via the `-p` flag and the
# injected prompt. Cline MUST NOT infer or switch modes on its own.
#
# ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │ MODE A: PLAN  (Cline invoked with -p / plan mode flag)                      │
# │                                                                             │
# │ Goal: produce the plan report. Nothing else.                                │
# │                                                                             │
# │ Permitted actions:                                                          │
# │   • Read any file in the repository                                         │
# │   • Write .forge/reports/<TASK_ID>_plan.md  (the only permitted write)     │
# │   • Update .forge/state/CURRENT_TASK.md  (set Step=PLAN, Status=COMPLETE)  │
# │                                                                             │
# │ Forbidden actions:                                                          │
# │   • Writing any source code, test, config, or CI file                      │
# │   • Running compilers, test runners, linters, or any build tool            │
# │   • Any git operation                                                       │
# │   • Any network call outside local filesystem reads                        │
# │                                                                             │
# │ Termination: After writing the report and updating CURRENT_TASK.md — STOP. │
# │ Do not wait for approval. Do not proceed to implementation.                 │
# │ The Forge handles the approval gate and resumes the pipeline.               │
# └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
# ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │ MODE B: ACT  (Cline invoked in act mode, approved plan injected)            │
# │                                                                             │
# │ Goal: implement the approved plan, run tests to zero failures, local-commit │
# │       in submodule repos, write the implementation report — then STOP.     │
# │                                                                             │
# │ Permitted actions:                                                          │
# │   • Read any file in the repository                                         │
# │   • Write/modify source files within the task's project repo               │
# │   • Write/modify test files and CI workflow files                           │
# │   • Run build tools, compilers, test runners, linters                      │
# │   • `git add -A` inside the project repo (STAGE ONLY — do not commit)     │
# │   • Write .forge/reports/<TASK_ID>_implement.md                            │
# │   • Update .forge/state/CURRENT_TASK.md                                    │
# │                                                                             │
# │ Forbidden actions:                                                          │
# │   • `git commit` — The Forge is the sole author of all commits             │
# │   • `git push` — The Forge pushes after push approval                      │
# │   • Any git operation outside the task's project repo                      │
# │   • Deviating from the approved plan (no scope creep)                      │
# │   • Deleting or modifying the _plan.md report for this task                │
# │                                                                             │
# │ Termination: After files are staged (git add -A) and the _implement.md    │
# │ report is written — STOP. The Forge commits, seeks approval, and pushes.   │
# └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘


# ── 3. PLAN REPORT FORMAT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Output path: forge/reports/<TASK_ID>_plan.md
#
# The report MUST use exactly the following structure. Sections are mandatory.
# Omitting a section or adding unlabelled free-text outside sections is an error.
# Do NOT include any model thinking, reasoning traces, or internal notes.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# # Plan Report: <TASK_ID>
#
# | Field       | Value                                      |
# |-------------|---------------------------------------------|
# | Task ID     | <TASK_ID>                                   |
# | Phase       | <NNN> — <Phase Name>                        |
# | Description | <task description>                          |
# | Depends on  | <comma-separated prereq IDs or "none">      |
# | Repos       | <comma-separated repo names>                |
# | Planned at  | <ISO 8601 UTC timestamp>                    |
# | Attempt     | <integer, 1 for first, increments on retry> |
#
# ## Objective
#
# One paragraph. What this task achieves and why it is needed.
#
# ## Scope
#
# Explicit enumeration of what IS and IS NOT in scope.
#
# ### In Scope
# - <item>
#
# ### Out of Scope
# - <item>
#
# ## Approach
#
# Step-by-step implementation strategy. Each step must be specific enough
# that a different agent could execute it deterministically.
#
# 1. <step>
# 2. <step>
#
# ## Files Affected
#
# | Action   | Path                              | Description            |
# |----------|-----------------------------------|------------------------|
# | CREATE   | <path>                            | <what it contains>     |
# | MODIFY   | <path>                            | <what changes>         |
# | DELETE   | <path>                            | <reason>               |
#
# ## Tests
#
# Enumerate every test that will be written or updated and what it validates.
#
# | Test ID / Name            | File                     | Validates               |
# |---------------------------|--------------------------|-------------------------|
# | <name>                    | <path>                   | <behaviour>             |
#
# ## CI Impact
#
# Describe any changes to .github/workflows/ci.yml required by this task.
# If no changes: state "No CI changes required."
#
# ## Risks and Mitigations
#
# | Risk                      | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation              |
# |---------------------------|-----------|--------|-------------------------|
# | <risk>                    | Low/Med/Hi | L/M/H  | <mitigation>            |
#
# ## Acceptance Criteria
#
# A checklist. Every item must be verifiable by running a command or
# inspecting a file. No subjective criteria.
#
# - [ ] <criterion>
# - [ ] <criterion>
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── 4. IMPLEMENTATION REPORT FORMAT ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Output path: forge/reports/<TASK_ID>_implement.md
#
# Written at the end of the ACT session, after all tests pass and local
# commits are made. Same structural discipline as the plan report.
# Sections are mandatory. No thinking traces, no reasoning, no filler.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# # Implementation Report: <TASK_ID>
#
# | Field            | Value                                      |
# |------------------|--------------------------------------------|
# | Task ID          | <TASK_ID>                                  |
# | Phase            | <NNN> — <Phase Name>                       |
# | Description      | <task description>                         |
# | Plan report      | forge/reports/<TASK_ID>_plan.md            |
# | Implemented at   | <ISO 8601 UTC timestamp>                   |
# | Test result      | PASS — <N> tests, 0 failures               |
#
# ## Summary
#
# One paragraph. What was built, key design decisions made during
# implementation, and any notable deviations from the plan (with justification).
# Deviations require explicit justification; silent scope changes are rejected.
#
# ## Files Changed
#
# | Action   | Path                              | Description            |
# |----------|-----------------------------------|------------------------|
# | CREATED  | <path>                            | <what it contains>     |
# | MODIFIED | <path>                            | <what changed>         |
# | DELETED  | <path>                            | <reason>               |
#
# ## Test Results
#
# Paste the final test runner output verbatim inside a code fence.
# All runs must show 0 failures before writing this report.
#
# ```
# <test runner output>
# ```
#
# ## CI Changes
#
# List every change made to CI workflow files. If none: "No CI changes made."
#
# ## Commit Log
#
# List every local commit made in each submodule repo (git log --oneline).
# Commits must follow Conventional Commits format:
#   <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Valid types:  feat | fix | test | docs | refactor | chore
# Valid scopes: anvilml-core | anvilml-ipc | anvilml-hardware | anvilml-registry
#               anvilml-worker | anvilml-scheduler | anvilml-server | py-worker
#               bloomeryui | root
#
# ### backend (AnvilML)
# ```
# <git log --oneline output>
# ```
#
# ### frontend (BloomeryUI)
# ```
# <git log --oneline output>
# ```
#
# ## Acceptance Criteria — Verification
#
# Reproduce the acceptance checklist from the plan report with each item
# marked as PASS or FAIL and the command or evidence used to verify it.
#
# | Criterion                 | Status | Evidence                        |
# |---------------------------|--------|---------------------------------|
# | <criterion from plan>     | PASS   | `cargo test -p anvilml-core`    |
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── 5. GIT RULES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# These rules are absolute. Violations break the pipeline and may corrupt the
# repository state.
#
# 5.1  Cline MUST NOT commit. `git commit` is exclusively executed by
#      The Forge. Cline only stages: `git add -A` inside the project repo.
#
# 5.2  Cline MUST NOT push to any remote. `git push` is exclusively
#      executed by The Forge after push approval.
#
# 5.3  Cline MUST NOT perform any git operation outside the task's
#      project repo.
#
# 5.4  Commit messages are authored by The Forge in Conventional Commits
#      format. Cline does not write commit messages.
#        <type>(<project>): <task_id> — <description>
#
#      Examples authored by The Forge:
#        feat(anvilml): P1-A3 — anvilml-core config types
#        fix(anvilml): P2-B1 — correct worker respawn race condition
#        docs(sindristudio): P1-A1 — repository scaffold and CI
#
# 5.5  Do not amend, rebase, or force-push any commit.
#
# 5.6  Do not create, delete, or rename branches.
#      All work is on the current branch (main).
#
# 5.7  Do not modify .gitmodules or any GitHub Actions workflow file
#      unless explicitly listed in the task's "Files Affected" table.


# ── 6. TASK ATOMICITY RULES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Tasks are intentionally small. Cline must implement exactly the task
# defined in the injected prompt — no more, no less.
#
# 6.1  Do not implement functionality not listed in the plan's "In Scope"
#      section, even if it would be "helpful" or "obviously needed".
#
# 6.2  Do not refactor code outside the files listed in "Files Affected"
#      unless a failing test in those files requires it.
#
# 6.3  Do not upgrade dependencies unless the task explicitly requires it.
#
# 6.4  Do not modify unrelated tests. Do not delete tests.
#
# 6.5  If a prerequisite task's output is missing or incomplete, STOP and
#      write the blocker to forge/reports/<TASK_ID>_plan.md or _implement.md
#      under a "## Blockers" section. Do not attempt to compensate.


# ── 7. TEST AND CI REQUIREMENTS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 7.1  Every task that writes source code MUST include tests.
#      No exceptions. "We'll add tests later" violates this rule.
#
# 7.2  The test suite for the affected crate/package must exit 0 before
#      Cline writes the implementation report or makes any commit.
#
# 7.3  The full workspace test suite (cargo test --workspace or equivalent)
#      must exit 0 before writing the implementation report.
#      Regressions in other crates caused by this task must be fixed.
#
# 7.4  Test file naming:
#      - Rust:       unit tests in same file (mod tests {}), integration
#                    tests in tests/<crate_name>_<feature>.rs
#      - TypeScript: <component>.test.ts alongside the component
#      - Python:     tests/test_<module>.py
#
# 7.5  When CI workflow files are modified, the change must:
#      - Preserve all existing jobs
#      - Add a new job or step only if the plan report specifies it
#      - Not disable or skip any existing test job
#
# 7.6  If tests fail after implementation, Cline MUST fix the failures
#      before writing the report. Test-fix is part of the ACT session.
#      Cline MUST NOT write the implementation report with known failures.


# ── 8. CONTEXT WINDOW MANAGEMENT ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 8.1  Context usage is monitored externally via context.log.
#      Cline should be aware that sessions run within CLINE_TIMEOUT (90 min).
#
# 8.2  At 50% context usage:  continue normally, note usage in internal planning.
#
# 8.3  At 65% context usage:  prioritise completing the current atomic step.
#      If mid-implementation, finish the current file, run tests, commit,
#      then write a partial implementation report with a "## Continuation"
#      section listing what remains. STOP cleanly so The Forge can resume.
#
# 8.4  Do not attempt to compress the task scope to fit the context window.
#      Write a clean partial report and stop; do not produce half-baked output.
#
# 8.5  The Forge will detect a partial implementation report and resume
#      the ACT session in a new Cline invocation with the partial report
#      injected as context.


# ── 9. PROHIBITED BEHAVIOURS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The following are unconditional prohibitions regardless of task context:
#
# 9.1  No git push, git push --force, or any remote write operation.
# 9.2  No modifications to forge.py, state.json, tasks.json, or forge/*.py.
# 9.3  No modifications to files outside the repos listed in the task's
#      "repos" field (e.g. if repos=["anvilml"], do not touch frontend/).
# 9.4  No use of environment variables, secrets, or API keys not already
#      present in the repository's documented configuration.
# 9.5  No network calls to external services (no npm publish, cargo publish,
#      Docker push, S3 upload, or equivalent).
# 9.6  No interactive prompts. All tool invocations must be non-interactive
#      (use -y, --yes, --non-interactive flags where applicable).
# 9.7  No spawning of background processes or daemons that outlive the session.
# 9.8  No modifications to .env files or secrets unless the task explicitly
#      lists a specific .env.example change in "Files Affected".
# 9.9  No self-modification: do not read, edit, or reason about .clinerules
#      as a target for modification. This file is read-only to Cline.


# ── 10. ERROR HANDLING AND STOPPING ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 10.1  If Cline encounters an unrecoverable error (missing prerequisite output,
#       environment misconfiguration, unresolvable build failure), it MUST:
#       a. Write a "## Blockers" section to the in-progress report file
#       b. Update forge/state/CURRENT_TASK.md with Status=BLOCKED
#       c. STOP immediately — do not guess, retry indefinitely, or continue
#          with a workaround that was not in the plan
#
# 10.2  Build failures that are within the task's scope (i.e., caused by code
#       written in this session) MUST be fixed before writing the report.
#       They are not blockers; they are part of the test-fix loop.
#
# 10.3  Build failures caused by pre-existing issues in the repository
#       (not introduced by this task) ARE blockers. Document and stop.
#
# 10.4  If a test runner produces flaky results (pass on retry), document
#       the flakiness in the implementation report under "## Test Results"
#       and ensure the final run shows 0 failures.


# ── 11. FILE AND PATH CONVENTIONS ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 11.1  Report files — inside the TARGET REPOSITORY:
#         .forge/reports/<TASK_ID>_plan.md       — written in PLAN session
#         .forge/reports/<TASK_ID>_implement.md  — written in ACT session
#       Paths are relative to the project repo root (e.g. AnvilML/).
#       .forge/ is a hidden directory, version-controlled in the project repo,
#       committed by The Forge as part of the post-approval commit.
#
# 11.2  State file — inside the TARGET REPOSITORY:
#         .forge/state/CURRENT_TASK.md
#       Must be updated at the end of every session.
#       Format:
#         Task: <TASK_ID>
#         Step: <PLAN|IMPLEMENT>
#         Status: <COMPLETE|BLOCKED>
#         Updated: <ISO 8601 UTC>
#
# 11.3  Phase task documents — inside the TARGET REPOSITORY:
#         docs/TASKS_PHASE<NNN>.md    (e.g. docs/TASKS_PHASE001.md)
#       Cline reads this but does not modify it.
#
# 11.4  Project scope: the task's "project" field names the single repository
#       Cline operates on. Cline MUST NOT read or write files outside that
#       repository. The Forge resolves the project name to an absolute path
#       via repos.json, which lives next to forge.py (not in any repository).
#
# 11.5  Do not create files at the repository root unless explicitly listed
#       in the plan's "Files Affected" table.


# ── 12. PHASE NUMBERING REFERENCE ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Phase numbers are zero-padded to three digits in filenames (001, 002 …)
# and displayed as plain integers in task IDs (P1-A3, not P001-A3).
# The canonical mapping of phase number to phase name is in docs/PHASES.md.
# Example mapping (authoritative source is always docs/PHASES.md):
#
#   001  Repository Scaffold & CI
#   002  AnvilML Core Types
#   003  AnvilML IPC Protocol
#   004  AnvilML Worker Management
#   005  AnvilML Scheduler
#   006  AnvilML HTTP/WS Server
#   007  Python Worker
#   008  BloomeryUI Foundation
#   009  BloomeryUI Node Graph
#   010  BloomeryUI Integration & E2E


# ── END OF .clinerules ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
